    </msItem>

    <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.3">
      <locus from="12r"></locus>
      <title type="complete" ref="LIT4668Prayer#Tuesday1">Protective prayer for Tuesday</title>
      <textLang mainLang="gez"></textLang>
      <incipit xml:lang="gez">በስመ፡ <gap reason="ellipsis" resp="PRS9602Turaev"></gap> ጸሎት፡ በእንተ፡ መልከ፡ ጼደቅ፡ ወበእንተ፡ ጰራቅሊጦስ፡ <foreign xml:lang="en">In the name of
    <gap reason="ellipsis" resp="PRS9602Turaev"></gap> a prayer of Melchizedek and Paraclete.</foreign></incipit>
    </msItem>
    <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.4">
      <locus from="15v"></locus>
      <title type="complete" ref="LIT4668Prayer#Tuesday2">The second protective prayer for Tuesday.</title>
      <textLang mainLang="gez"></textLang>
      <incipit xml:lang="gez">ጸሎተ፡ ምሕረት፡ ዘጸለዩ፡ መላእክት፡ ወሰማዕት፡ ጳጳሳት፡ ካህናት፡ <foreign xml:lang="en">Prayer of mercy, which is pronounced by angels, martyrs, bishops, priests.</foreign></incipit>
    </msItem>
    <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.5">
      <locus from="19r"></locus>
      <title type="complete" ref="LIT2000Mazmur#Ps120">Psalm 120.</title>
      <textLang mainLang="gez"></textLang>
    </msItem>
    <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.6">
      <locus from="19v"></locus>
      <title type="complete" ref="LIT4668Prayer#Wednesday3"></title>
      <textLang mainLang="gez"></textLang>
      <incipit xml:lang="gez">በስመ፡ <gap reason="ellipsis" resp="PRS9602Turaev"></gap> ጸሎተ፡ ሥርዓተ፡ እምነቶሙ፡ ለሐዋርያት፡ ወድኃኒተ፡ ነፍስ፡ ወሥጋ፡ ወመንጽሔ፡ ኃጢአት፡ <foreign xml:lang="gez">The prayer
    of the ordination of the faith of the Apostles, the salvation of soul and body, and purification of sins.</foreign></incipit>
    </msItem>
    <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.7">
      <locus from="23r"></locus>
      <title type="complete" corresp="LIT4668Prayer#Wednesday2">Protective prayer for Thursday</title>
      <textLang mainLang="gez"></textLang>
      <incipit xml:lang="gez">በስመ፡ <gap reason="ellipsis" resp="PRS9602Turaev"></gap> ወይቤልዎ፡ መላእክት፡ ታስተኃፍሮሙ፡ ለእለ፡ ደገምዎ፡</incipit>
    </msItem>
    <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.8">
      <locus from="30r"></locus>
      <title type="complete" ref="LIT4668Prayer#Friday">Protective prayer for Friday.</title>
      <textLang mainLang="gez"></textLang>
      <incipit xml:lang="gez">በስመ፡ <gap reason="ellipsis" resp="PRS9602Turaev"></gap> ቅዱሳን፡ አስማቲሁ፡ ለክርስቶስ፡</incipit>
    </msItem>
    <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.9">
      <locus from="36r"></locus>
      <title type="complete" ref="LIT4668Prayer#Saturday">Protective prayer for Saturday.</title>
      <textLang mainLang="gez"></textLang>
      <incipit xml:lang="gez">በስመ፡ <gap reason="ellipsis" resp="PRS9602Turaev"></gap> ጸሎተ፡ ሥርየተ፡ ኃጢአት፡ ወሥርየተ፡ እምነቶሙ፡ ለሐዋርያት፡ ወለኲሎሙ፡ ፸ወ፪አርድእት፡ ከማሁ፡ ይቤሎሙ፡ ለአርዳኢሁ፡
    ኢየሱስ፡ አንትሙ፡ ውእቱ፡ አዕርክትየ፡ <foreign xml:lang="en">The prayer of remission of sins and forgiveness of the faith of the Apostles and all 72 disciples, as Jesus said to His disciples: 'You are my friends!'</foreign></incipit>
    </msItem>
    <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.10">
      <locus from="43r"></locus>
      <title type="complete" ref="LIT2000Mazmur#Ps139">Psalm 139</title>
      <textLang mainLang="gez"></textLang>
    </msItem>
    <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.11">
      <locus from="44r"></locus>
      <title type="complete" ref="LIT4668Prayer#Sunday">Protective prayer for Sunday.</title>
      <textLang mainLang="gez"></textLang>
      <incipit xml:lang="gez">በስመ፡ <gap reason="ellipsis" resp="PRS9602Turaev"></gap> በርናኤል፡ አጉዳኤል፡ ፍለኤል፡ ዘንተ፡ እስማተ፡ ዘወሀቦ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡ ለአናንያ፡ ወአዛርያ፡ ወሚሳኤል፡
      <foreign xml:lang="en">In the name of <gap reason="ellipsis" resp="PRS9602Turaev"></gap> Barnāʾel, ʾAgudāʾel, Fǝlaʾel - these are the names, which God gave to Ananias, Azariah, and Mishael.</foreign></incipit>
    </msItem>
    <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.12">
      <locus from="48r"></locus>
      <title type="complete" ref="LIT4668Prayer#Andrew">Another protective prayer for Sunday</title>
      <textLang mainLang="gez"></textLang>
      <incipit xml:lang="gez">በስመ፡ <gap reason="ellipsis" resp="PRS9602Turaev"></gap> አስማተ፡ ዘነገሮ፡ እግዚእነ፡ ለቅዱስ፡ እንድርያስ፡ ረድዕ፡ ሐዋርያ፡ ወሰማዕት፡ <gap reason="ellipsis" resp="PRS9602Turaev"></gap>
    ወይቤሎ፡ ሑር፡ በሀገረ፡ በላዕተ፡ ሰብእ፡ <foreign xml:lang="en">In the name of <gap reason="ellipsis" resp="PRS9602Turaev"></gap> Names, which Our Lord told to St Andrew, the disciple, Apostle, and martyr
  <gap reason="ellipsis" resp="PRS9602Turaev"></gap> And he told him: 'Go to the country of cannibals!'</foreign></incipit>
    </msItem>
    <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.13">
      <locus from="52r"></locus>
      <title type="complete" ref="LIT2000Mazmur#Ps51">Psalm 51.</title>
